Culture is the complex whole of [shared patterns of human activity](1) and the [symbolic structures](3) that give such activity significance, all of which are [learned and transmitted among members of a group.](6)
shared patterns of human activity, including a group's language, customs, social institutions, and its production of [art and technology.](1)
art for aesthetic expression and technology for practical application
symbolic structures, such as beliefs, values, and [myths,](1)
myths that provide a [collective narrative](1) about the world
collective narrative that explains a society's origins, purpose, and moral order
learned and transmitted through a process of [socialization and enculturation.](1)
socialization from community interaction and enculturation from direct teaching.